  abstract  = {The design of traction mechanisms of continuous conveying units (e.g. plastic chains) is so far based on a purely mechanical dimensioning. However, mechanical limits are only applicable in a limited way to avoid system failure. With higher speeds or pressure, especially the thermal stress increases, which results in system failure based on softening or melting of the materials at a certain temperature. By means of systematic studies, correlations between friction temperature, coefficient of friction, wear and process parameters are examined. On this basis, a model for calculating the friction temperature is developed.},
